  <mainDescription>System trustworthiness is measured while designing, developing, or operating the system.</mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The skills required are similar to those of the risk analyzer in the Capability Threat and mitigation controls&#xD;
        identification.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Many (most) of the tasks at runtime can be automated.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_E9kMMBoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA" name="Import or Update the System status " guid="_E9kMMBoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA">
    <sectionDescription>Identify the current system assets and topology.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Huqa0BoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA" name="Import or Update Trustworthiness Certificates" guid="_Huqa0BoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA">
    <sectionDescription>Import or update the trustworthiness certificate of each asset in the system.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_KWYrABoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA" name="Import or Update the Threats Activity" guid="_KWYrABoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA">
    <sectionDescription>Using a designed threat model, or updating this model with new threats that have been identified or others that are not&#xD;
active.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_M-sxEBoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA" name="Import or Update Controls" guid="_M-sxEBoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA">
    <sectionDescription>The designed threat model already contains a set of controls for each pre-identified threat. In some cases these exiting&#xD;
controls need to be modified. If new threats are identified, a set of controls should e allocated to the new threats.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_OixL4BoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA" name="Compute Trustworthiness" guid="_OixL4BoPEeOeTN_guLSnBA">
    <sectionDescription>Invoke the trustworthiness calculator.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Provide an architect or monitor with timely trustworthiness metrics.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
